// how to update all packages of your system
sudo apt-get update // Update is used to resynchronize the package index files from their sources on Ubuntu Linux via the Internet.
sudo apt-get upgrade -y // Upgrade is used to install the newest versions of all packages currently installed on the Ubuntu system.


